<TEXTAREA wrap=hard NAME="comment" ROWS="30" COLS="76" >政景＠鬼兜．E'ciさんは No.7023「PoS MNK2」で書きました。
>You say, 'I choose Wu'
>Holwin says 'Take this and read it.  Once you are finished, I will summon 
>the Tranquil's most enlightened follower. 
>
>Holwin から Strength を受け取り、返します。
>
>Holwin says 'Farewell. 
>Wu the Enlightened says 'Peace to you, my child. 
>
>Wu the Enlightened が現われ、Holwin が消えました。
>
>You say, 'Hail Wu the Enlightened'
>Wu the Enlightened says 'Greetings, warrior of mind and body.  To prove 
>your worth to me, you must complete a test.  Which test do you wish to 
>take?  I will permit you to take the test of tears, fists, or 
>tranquility. 
>
>You say, 'I choose tears.'
>Wu the Enlightened says 'The test of tears involves knowing when to 
>release, and when to provide a shoulder for another.  Bring me a spiroc 
>statuette, a spiroc talon, and a silken wrap.  I will teach you the way. 
>
>You say, 'I choose fists.'
>Wu the Enlightened says 'A monk must know when to use his or her fists, 
>and when to use the mind.  In this endeavor, you must decide which you 
>shall use.  Return to me, once you have found them, a pair of brass 
>knuckles, a white spiroc feather, an ethereal amethyst, and a nebulous 
>sapphire. 
>
>You say, 'I choose tranquility.'
>Wu the Enlightened says 'Ah, the test of tranquility.  Only the tranquil 
>monk can achieve enlightenment.  Are you such an individual?  Time shall 
>tell.  Retrieve these items for me.  Bring an aged nectar, a Writ of 
>Quellious, and a Tear of Quellious.  Then we shall assess your ability.
</TEXTAREA><br>
</td></tr>
